{"id": "4215", "post": "<div class=\"post-4215 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-virtual-servers tag-canada tag-montreal tag-openvz tag-servarica-com tag-windows tag-xen tag-xen-pv\" id=\"post-4215\"><h2 class=\"storytitle\"><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/servarica-7month-1gb-windows-xen-hvm-or-1-5gb-linux-pv-in-montreal-canada/\" rel=\"bookmark\">Servarica \u2013 $7/Month 1GB Windows XEN HVM or 1.5GB Linux PV in Montreal, Canada</a></h2><div class=\"meta\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" data-src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" alt=\"Tags: \" class=\"litespeed-loaded\" data-was-processed=\"true\"> <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/canada/\" rel=\"tag\">canada</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/montreal/\" rel=\"tag\">Montreal</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/openvz/\" rel=\"tag\">openvz</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/servarica-com/\" rel=\"tag\">servarica.com</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/windows/\" rel=\"tag\">windows</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/xen/\" rel=\"tag\">xen</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/xen-pv/\" rel=\"tag\">Xen-PV</a> <img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" alt=\"Date/Time: \" class=\"litespeed-loaded\" data-was-processed=\"true\"> August 21, 2013 @ 11:44 pm, by Liam</div><div class=\"storycontent tablelook\"><p><a href=\"http://servarica.com\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/serveracia.jpg.webp\" class=\"screenshot litespeed-loaded\" alt=\"Servarica\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/serveracia.jpg.webp\" data-was-processed=\"true\"></a>Hani, from <a href=\"http://servarica.com\">Servarica</a>, has got three offers for us located in Canada. With recent political issues, Canada\u2019s quick pings to America, and more liberal internet policies (no PRISIM and patriot act), could appeal to some.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>LEB Special 1</strong><p></p><ul><li>1.5GB RAM</li><li>2 vCPU Cores</li><li>20GB SAN Diskspace</li><li>1TB Bandwidth</li><li>1Gbps Port Speed</li><li>1 IPv4 Address</li><li>Xen PV &amp; Linux</li><li>$7/Month | <a href=\"https://servarica.com/clients/cart.php?a=add&amp;pid=154\" target=\"_blank\">Order Link</a></li></ul></td><td><strong>LEB Special 2</strong><p></p><ul><li>512MB RAM</li><li>2 vCPU Cores</li><li>12GB SAN Diskspace</li><li>1TB Bandwidth</li><li>1Gbps Port Speed</li><li>1 IPv4 Address</li><li>Xen PV &amp; Linux</li><li>$3.80/Month | <a href=\"https://servarica.com/clients/cart.php?a=add&amp;pid=160\" target=\"_blank\">Order Link</a></li></ul></td><td><strong>Windows 1</strong><p></p><ul><li>1024MB RAM</li><li>2 vCPU Cores</li><li>24GB SAN Diskspace</li><li>1TB Bandwidth</li><li>1Gbps Port Speed</li><li>1 IPv4 Address</li><li>Xen HVM &amp; Win 08</li><li>$7.00/Month | <a href=\"https://servarica.com/clients/cart.php?a=add&amp;pid=159\" target=\"_blank\">Order Link</a></li></ul></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Servarica have been a registered company in province of Quebec for more than 2 years. We have featured them <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/servarica-6-99-256mb-xen-vps-in-canada/\">once before</a>, and that was over 2 years ago! As well as being a VPS provider, they\u2019re also a software house who develop control panel / management software for Citrix XenServers. Their nodes are using brand new Supermicro servers with 2 X E5-2560, ECC DDR3 memory and \u201chigh end redundant networking devices\u201d. This infrastructure will be the basis of their future cloud offering. The OS for windows will be Windows Server 2008 R2 SP1 (Datacenter edition). Please leave your reviews below.<br>\n<span id=\"more-4215\"></span><br>\nServarica accept payments via Paypal (credit cards are accepted through paypal). For this offer, they\u2019re providing a 7 days full refund policy with no question asked. Canadians will have to pay GST and PST tax. They offer a 99.9% uptime guarantee, with SLAs if they fail that. Some orders may take up to 24 hours to be processed. Additional IPs are billed at $1.50 CAD per month. High availability and backups can also be added at checkout for an extra fee. IPv6 will be available soon. You can combine more than one of these plans into a bigger VPS (simply state in order notes). Their TOS/AUP can be <a href=\"http://servarica.com/terms-of-service/\">viewed here</a>.</p><p><strong>Network Information:</strong></p><p>Servers are located at the Cologix Datacenter in Montreal. They operate their our own multi-homed network and have their own AS number. Their network is fully redundant with redundant routers and switches.</p><p>Test IPv4: 204.93.54.203<br>\nTest File: <a href=\"http://204.93.54.203/file_100MB.bin\">http://204.93.54.203/file_100MB.bin</a></p><p class=\"dpsp-share-text\"></p><div id=\"dpsp-content-bottom\" class=\"dpsp-content-wrapper dpsp-shape-rounded dpsp-column-auto dpsp-has-spacing dpsp-no-labels dpsp-show-on-mobile dpsp-button-style-1 dpsp-has-icon-background dpsp-has-button-background dpsp-show-total-share-count dpsp-show-total-share-count-after\"><ul class=\"dpsp-networks-btns-wrapper dpsp-networks-btns-content dpsp-has-button-icon-animation\"><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Flowendbox.com%2Fblog%2Fservarica-7month-1gb-windows-xen-hvm-or-1-5gb-linux-pv-in-montreal-canada%2F&amp;t=Servarica%20-%20%247%2FMonth%201GB%20Windows%20XEN%20HVM%20or%201.5GB%20Linux%20PV%20in%20Montreal%2C%20Canada\" class=\"dpsp-network-btn dpsp-facebook dpsp-no-label dpsp-first\" title=\"Share on Facebook\"><span class=\"dpsp-network-icon\"></span><span class=\"dpsp-network-label-wrapper\"></span></a></li><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=Servarica%20-%20%247%2FMonth%201GB%20Windows%20XEN%20HVM%20or%201.5GB%20Linux%20PV%20in%20Montreal%2C%